headline: Tyler Technologies beats quarterly revenue estimates on steady cloud demand
summary: Tyler Technologies beat Wall Street expectations for second-quarter revenue on Wednesday, helped by steady demand for its IT and cloud-based software services. Shares of the company rose about 3% in extended trading. Demand for Tyler's services has grown as more businesses and government agencies transition to cloud-based solutions to streamline operations.

headline: Tyler Technologies: Q2 Earnings Snapshot
summary: PLANO, Texas (AP) — Tyler Technologies Inc. TYL) on Wednesday reported second-quarter net income of $84.6 million. On a per-share basis, the Plano, Texas-based company said it had net income of $1.93.
